  38. ‌  val check: t -> Module_name.t -> Digest.t -> filepath -> unit
  39.         (* [check tbl name crc source]
  40.              checks consistency of ([name], [crc]) with infos previously
  41.              stored in [tbl].  If no CRC was previously associated with
  42.              [name], record ([name], [crc]) in [tbl].
  43.              [source] is the name of the file from which the information
  44.              comes from.  This is used for error reporting. *)

  46. ‌  val check_noadd: t -> Module_name.t -> Digest.t -> filepath -> unit
  47.         (* Same as [check], but raise [Not_available] if no CRC was previously
  48.              associated with [name]. *)

  50. ‌  val source: t -> Module_name.t -> filepath
  51.         (* [source tbl name] returns the file name associated with [name]
  52.            if the latter has an associated CRC in [tbl].
  53.            Raise [Not_found] otherwise. *)

  55. ‌  val extract: Module_name.t list -> t -> (Module_name.t * Digest.t option) list
  56.         (* [extract tbl names] returns an associative list mapping each string
  57.            in [names] to the CRC associated with it in [tbl]. If no CRC is
  58.            associated with a name then it is mapped to [None]. *)

  60. ‌  val extract_map : Module_name.Set.t -> t -> Digest.t option Module_name.Map.t
  61.         (* Like [extract] but with a more sophisticated type. *)

  63. ‌  val filter: (Module_name.t -> bool) -> t -> unit
  64.         (* [filter pred tbl] removes from [tbl] table all (name, CRC) pairs
  65.            such that [pred name] is [false]. *)

  67.   exception Inconsistency of {

  71.   }
  72.   (* Raised by [check] when a CRC mismatch is detected. *)
